Dude, you realize this is going to be so awesome.

181
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:56,129
- 我们要一醉方休  - 如何？
- We're going to pop ten bottles. - Think so?

182
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:58,408
我讨厌那条看门狗
I hate this doorman.

183
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:03,691
亚当·坎西迪 说了我会回来的
Adam Cassidy. Told you I'd be back.

184
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:08,370
你们的桌子在这边 先生
Your table's right this way, sir.

185
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:10,409
太好了！
Yeah!

186
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:13,370
太棒了
Yeah!

187
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:15,170
- 干！  - 干！
- Shots! - Shots!

188
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:16,845
- 干！  - 上帝啊
- Shots! - Oh my God.

189
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:20,898
今晚还不走运
if you guys don't get lucky tonight,

190
00:12:20,898 --> 00:12:22,051
以后就别想了
it's never going to happen.

191
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,043
我负责倒酒 你要来一份吗？
I'm fielding offers. You want in?

192
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:27,321
待会见
See me after.

193
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,480
干杯 伙计们！
Cheers, guys!

194
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:38,121
亚当 桌上的酒快没了
Adam, maybe we should close out the tab.

195
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:40,601
别担心
Hey, don't worry about it, man, don't worry about it.

196
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,330
我们能再来一瓶诗珞珂吗？
(全球百大高档烈酒品牌)
Hey, can we get another bottle of Ciroc?

197
00:12:43,280 --> 00:12:45,726
- 绕着我跳！  - 不 不 不
- Twirl me! - No, no, no.

198
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:49,607
来吧！
Come on!

199
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:26,371
伙计 你去哪儿
Hey, buddy, where you going?

200
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:29,528
走桃花运了
Could be love.

201
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:14,521
醒醒
Wake up.

202
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:23,728
醒醒
Hey, wake up.

203
00:14:23,920 --> 00:14:26,287
我得走了
I have to go.

204
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:27,885
你也该走了
So do you.

205
00:14:31,680 --> 00:14:32,886
没早餐吗？
No breakfast?

206
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:36,646
我做错什么了吗？
Did I, uh, do something wrong?

207
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:38,711
要是你做错了
If you had done something wrong,

208
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:40,566
你不可能还在这里
you wouldn't be here, would you?

209
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:43,963
那么…
So...

210
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:46,282
那么 我们…
So, uh, we...

211
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:48,681
…走吧
...are leaving.

212
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:54,326
等一下 我都不知道你叫什么
Wait a second, I don't even know your name.

213
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:58,406
你是要走消防梯吗？
Are you taking the fire escape?

214
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:02,126
好的
OK.

215
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:07,362
- 谢谢  - 不客气
- Thank you. - You're welcome.

216
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:16,764
清咖还是加糖奶咖？
Hey. Black, or cream and sugar?

217
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:17,942
你跟踪我？
You stalking me now?

218
00:15:17,942 --> 00:15:19,366
我只是想问问你叫什么
I just want to know your name.

219
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:22,882
你泡我 向我示好就是了电话号码？
Why? So you can poke me, friend me, ask for my number?

220
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:25,327
是的 给一个联系方式吧
Or you could just give me your number.

221
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,766
你不是我的菜
You're not relationship material.

222
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:28,445
菜？你想要长久关系？
Relationship? You're looking for a relationship?

223
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:30,284
我喜欢长久关系 我很在行
I love relationships. I'm great at relationships.

224
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:33,404
不 实际上我只想赶紧甩掉你
No. Actually, I'm just trying to get rid of you nicely.

225
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:35,884
我们炒饭了吗？
Didn't we have sex?

226
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:40,564
我喝醉的时候更中意桥那边的人
I have a thing for bridge-and-tunnel guys when I drink.

227
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:42,927
你刚才叫我桥那边的人？
Did you just call me bridge-and-tunnel?

228
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:45,325
你带我去吃芝士薯条
You took me out for cheese fries.

229
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:47,801
芝士薯条！
Cheese fries!

230
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:49,166
然后呢？
Oh. Then what?

231
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:51,641
然后一夜情呗
Then you had the night of your life.

232
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:53,251
你的原话
Your words, not mine.

233
00:15:54,480 --> 00:15:56,926
清咖
Oh... Black.

234
00:16:04,488 --> 00:16:07,949
（16条未读短信）

235
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:31,971
亚当·坎西迪？我是迈尔斯·米彻姆
Adam Cassidy? My name is Miles Meachum.

236
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:36,083
怀特先生想和你聊聊
Mr. Wyatt would like to speak with you.

237
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:41,250
你怎么知道我在这里？
How did you know where I was?

238
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,207
我都不住这附近的
I mean, I don't even live around here.

239
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:04,050
坎西迪先生
Mr. Cassidy.

240
00:17:05,080 --> 00:17:08,084
自称比我还了解我生意的人
The man who claims he knows my business better than I do.

241
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:09,765
请坐吧
Here, take a seat.

242
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:14,130
- 来杯葡萄酒？  - 不
- Drop of vino? - Uh... No.

243
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:19,205
看来你是我们帐务漏洞的受益者
It seems you were the beneficiary of an accounting error we made.

244
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,051
我不知道你在说什么
I don't know what you're talking about.

245
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:24,009
Ethion开发基金帐户
The Ethion discretionary fund.

246
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:27,886
我的钱用在哪里了？
Where's my money?

247
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:30,122
用于市场研究调研报告
We used it on market research.

248
00:17:30,280 --> 00:17:32,726
调研RISE俱乐部？
At Club Rise?

249
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:34,370
1万6千美元？
Sixteen grand?

250
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:37,683
看来这份调研报告必然很详尽
It must be a very detailed report.

251
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,881
你认为你能侥幸成功么？
You think you can rip me off and get away with it?

252
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:42,411
信用卡诈骗
Credit card fraud?

253
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:44,642
不 对不起 我会还回来的
No, sir, I'm sorry. I'm gonna pay you back.

254
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:48,043
不行 这又不是贷款
No you won't. It wasn't a loan.

255
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:51,931
给你两条路
Now there's two ways we can play this.

256
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:54,481
做马还是做狗？
Are you a horse or a dog?

257
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:57,769
马是恐惧被鞭笞而飞奔
A horse is motivated by fear. He's running from the whip.

258
00:17:57,920 --> 00:17:59,922
这鞭子就是信用卡诈骗
The whip here being felony fraud.

259
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:02,686
- 他是狗  - 狗是被饥饿而驱使
- He's a dog. - A dog is motivated by hunger.

260
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:04,922
他追踪兔子作为下一顿美食
He's chasing the rabbit, his next meal.

261
00:18:05,080 --> 00:18:07,765
你在布鲁克林低收入家庭长大
You were raised in a low-income home in Brooklyn.

262
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:10,127
七岁的时候妈妈死了
Your mother died when you were seven.

263
00:18:10,280 --> 00:18:12,726
税务显示你还要赡养老父
Your W-2 says you now support your father.

264
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:13,927
那？
30?

265
00:18:14,080 --> 00:18:16,048
那意味着你每天都要翻过跨海大桥
So, it means you came across that bridge every day

266
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:17,605
渴望成功
hungry to succeed.

267
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:19,922
- 人都想成功  - 但并非人人可以像我们这样
- Everyone wants to succeed. - Yeah, but not like us.

268
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:23,289
你父亲做了32年保安
Your father spent 32 years as a security guard.

269
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:25,807
- 那行业能有什么雄心壮志？  - 这到底在干嘛？
- Where's the ambition in that? - What's this about?

270
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:28,162
你渴求更多！
You want more out of life!

271
00:18:28,320 --> 00:18:32,211
我曾经和你一样 只不过来自不同的街区
I grew up like you. I mean, different streets.

272
00:18:32,360 --> 00:18:35,807
怀着相同的梦 但没人会替我实现 没人
Same dream, but nobody gave it to me. No one.

273
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:39,203
我说我能让你发财如何 ？
And what if I told you I could make you rich?

274
00:18:39,360 --> 00:18:41,169
让你朋友们重新获得工作？
And give your friends their jobs back?

275
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,082
你昨天展示了一个绝佳的创意
That was a smart pitch you gave yesterday.

276
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:52,410
我从艾康公司起家
I started out at Eikon.

277
00:18:55,120 --> 00:18:57,327
乔克·戈达是我的师傅
Jock Goddard was my mentor.

278
00:18:58,320 --> 00:19:00,209
你知道他吗
Do you know him?

279
00:19:00,360 --> 00:19:02,169
是的 我当然知道
Yeah, of course I know him.

280
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:04,527
我的毕业论文是半导体内存研究
I did my graduate thesis on semi-conductor memory.

281
00:19:04,680 --> 00:19:08,002
当时戈达要求手机不超过砖块大小
Goddard's basically the reason cell phones aren't the size of bricks.

282
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:09,127
他创建了艾康公司
He founded Eikon.

283
00:19:09,280 --> 00:19:11,169
并最终成功上市
And built it into the largest publicly traded

284
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:12,890
成为全世界最大的科技公司
technology company in the world.

285
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:14,690
自从我独立门户后
And ever since I left, he has spent

286
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:17,008
他无时不刻不想摧毁我
every waking moment trying to destroy me.

287
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:20,960
艾康公司马上要发布一款力挽狂澜的新智能手机
Eikon has a new smartphone coming that's said to be a game-changer.

288
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:22,770
代号Occura
They're calling it Occura.

289
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:25,446
你要去艾康公司工作
You are going to work for Eikon.

290
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:28,120
- 什么？  - 帮我们得到想要的 你可得50万
- What? - Get us in the door, you get 500K.

291
00:19:28,280 --> 00:19:30,851
成功之后 你会得到100万股权
Get us what we need, you'll see another million in stock options.

292
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,001
那笔数目
Money like that

293
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:34,003
足以让你安心照顾你父亲
would allow you to take care of your father and a whole lot more.

294
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:36,242
艾康公司不会雇佣我的
Eikon's not just going to hire me.

295
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:38,920
他们会 我们已经安排妥当
They will when we're done with you.

296
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:43,689
窃取商业机密是违法的
This is illegal. It's stealing trade secrets.

297
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:46,889
这就是你一直在等待的机会
This is the opportunity you have been waiting for.

298
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:48,365
不仅能让你夜夜笙歌
Now, you could have done a lot of things

299
00:19:48,365 --> 00:19:49,401
一如昨晚
with that credit card last night.

300
00:19:49,560 --> 00:19:52,378
而且还能支付你父亲的医疗保险费
Your father's health insurance premium,

301
00:19:52,378 --> 00:19:53,929
及学业贷款
graduate school loans,

302
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:57,203
可你决定搬出群居屋
but you decided to take your mates out on the town,

303
00:19:57,203 --> 00:19:58,165
住市中心的独立大宅
living it large.

304
00:19:58,320 --> 00:20:01,164
因为你必须熟悉另一半人的生活
Because you want to know how the other half lives.

305
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:04,210
另一半人即我们富人！
We are the other half!

306
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:07,762
这些我都能替你办到
That's what I'm offering you.

307
00:20:08,960 --> 00:20:10,041
如果我拒绝呢？
If I say no?

308
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:14,046
你和你朋友们将受到最严厉的法律追究
You and your friends will be prosecuted to the full extent of the law.

309
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:17,503
你不会只想坐着
And you don't want to sit around

310
00:20:17,503 --> 00:20:19,524
看我沏茶吧？
and watch me make tea, do you?

311
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:52,328
你谁啊 电视警察？
What are you, the TV police?

312
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:55,126
- 你睡着了  - 我只是闭闭眼
- You were asleep. - My eyes were closed.

313
00:20:55,280 --> 00:20:57,089
你去哪？
Where you going?

314
00:20:57,240 --> 00:20:59,010
公司放假
I caught a break at the company.

315
00:20:59,010 --> 00:21:00,528
放假 哪种假？
A break, what kind of break?

316
00:21:00,680 --> 00:21:02,142
足够支付房租
A kind of break that pays our rent

317
00:21:02,142 --> 00:21:03,604
和护士费用的假
and keeps your pretty nurse around.

318
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:05,489
是培训来着 我整个周末都要忙
It's a training thing, so I'll be gone all weekend.

319
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:06,361
今天周五
It's Friday night.

320
00:21:06,361 --> 00:21:08,450
不是说好去本齐奥吃披萨喝啤酒的吗？
I thought we were going to Benzio's for pizza and beer.

321
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:09,483
我要去上班了 爸爸
I got to work, Dad.

322
00:21:09,483 --> 00:21:11,649
如此才能飞黄腾达
That's how you climb the ladder in this business.

323
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:13,768
就因为你比手下干得更卖力
You work harder than the guy below you.

324
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:16,247
结果只能干一辈子的苦力保安
Otherwise you get stuck doing the same job your whole life.

325
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:23,448
听着
Look...

326
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:28,802
这些钱给你电话定餐 好吗？
Here's some money. You can order in, OK?

327
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:31,247
不要 多谢
No, no. Thanks.

328
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:33,886
好了
All right.

329
00:21:57,480 --> 00:22:00,484
你具体在公司做什么 朱迪斯？
What exactly do you do for the company, Judith?

330
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:04,166
我有行为心理学的博士学位
I have a PhD in behavioral psychology.

331
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:07,164
能告诉你为什么你至今尚未成功
I can take one look at you and tell you why you haven't succeeded.

332
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:09,163
不如敞开天窗说亮话吧？
Why don't you tell me how you really feel?

333
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:10,845
我有各种方式能令你…
I can give you the tools to ascend

334
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:13,321
跻身全美的上流社会
to the highest ranks of corporate America.

335
00:22:13,480 --> 00:22:15,289
但首先你得端正态度
But you have to lose the attitude.

336
00:22:56,520 --> 00:22:57,760
这边
This way.

337
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:02,046
我带你去房间
I'll show you to your room.

338
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:33,771
初次见面时
When we meet someone,

339
00:23:33,771 --> 00:23:36,609
形成所谓的第一印象
an immediate cognitive process takes place.

340
00:23:36,760 --> 00:23:39,843
通常会以貌取人
We construct our first ideas on them based on their appearance.

341
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,322
所以你要想被人接受
So, if you want to be accepted,

342
00:23:42,322 --> 00:23:44,210
就必须洞窥其中
you have to look the part.

343
00:23:45,160 --> 00:23:48,004
融入并进入他们的生活
You have to fit in to get in.

344
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:50,288
怀特和戈达间发生了什么事？
What happened with Wyatt and Goddard?

345
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:51,680
乔克戈达是个聪明的生意人
Jack's a brilliant businessman.

346
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:54,388
他总是能够在他的产品中
He was always able to imbue his products

347
00:23:54,388 --> 00:23:56,004
融入许多神奇的理念
with a magic of big ideas,

348
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:57,770
而怀特则是大脑
but Wyatt was the brains.

349
00:23:57,920 --> 00:23:58,762
没有他的设计
Without his designs,

350
00:23:58,762 --> 00:24:00,207
再神奇的理念都不能付诸实现
none of it would have been possible.

351
00:24:00,360 --> 00:24:02,283
听起来是完美的搭档啊
Hmm. Sounds like a perfect pairing.

352
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:03,631
对戈达 算是
For Goddard, yes.

353
00:24:03,631 --> 00:24:06,411
怀特献出了一生中最好的时光
Wyatt gave him the best years of his life.

354
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:12,284
乔克戈达失去了儿子迪兰 因为服毒过量
Jock lost his son Dylan to a drug overdose.

355
00:24:12,440 --> 00:24:15,046
所以 如果你谈到失去母亲…
So, if you talk about losing your mother...

356
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:17,806
不 我不会的
No, I won't.

357
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:21,726
会勾起他的回忆 趁机说你缺少父爱
Then, appeal to his void. Say you had no father figure.

358
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:23,291
我父亲还健在
